messages.content:
Hi @everyone

Starting today, position size limits will be based on notional USD value rather than base currency amounts.

Our old system set limits using the coin's base currency. When prices move significantly, those limits become misaligned.

After the recent market drawdown, many coins had effective position limits that were far smaller than intended, not because of any risk concern, but simply because prices dumped.

This created an awkward situation where we'd need to constantly adjust base currency limits to maintain consistent exposure, or leave limits that don't reflect current market conditions.

This has now been fixed.

Now, instead of "max 50,000 XYZ tokens" limits are now expressed as "max $X notional exposure."

This means:

- Limits automatically stay proportional as prices move
- We can actively adjust based on current volatility conditions.
- Position sizing stays consistent with intended risk parameters.

The sizing buckets are $50k, $100k, $150k, and $200k.

Coins are grouped into buckets based on liquidity and volatility characteristics, with limits reviewed and adjusted regularly.

We welcome your feedback with regard to listings and how we've bucketed our current assets, so please let us know if you think a specific coin should be bumped up a tier and we'll review.

**BTC and ETH have limits of $1M i.e. your only limit is the leverage available on your account size.**

You can review these here: https://www.breakoutprop.com/symbols/

We've also removed the maximum position size per order - this is managed by the overall maximum position size now.

This means you can execute the full size in 1 order without having to split it up, but please be aware that some of these alts are less liquid than others so you may incur slippage if you use a market order using the maximum position size.

This change opens the door to more listings. There were coins we'd held off listing due to the complexity of managing base currency limits during price swings.
Since this limitation no longer applies, listings have resumed.

You will find **Lighter** and **Zcash** listed in the terminal and already live.

Additionally, **we have reduced swap fees from 18% annualized to 12% annualized**.

This change is effective immediately and applies to all accounts, no action is required on your part.
